      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2024-03-14</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2024-12-02T17:24:40Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;This bill creates a good faith exception to certain fines imposed by the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Currently, the USPTO may reduce patent-related fees for small and micro entities, and an entity that falsely claims a fee reduction shall be subject to a fine. This bill exempts an entity from such a fine if the entity made a good faith assertion or certification that the entity was entitled to a fee reduction.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
